[This virus is spreading rapidly across the continent. It is devastating to the flocks it affects, and has a profound impact on producers, state and federal personnel, and especially on the affected birds.

This virus demands we all take extreme precautions to protect the birds, and to be extremely vigilant regarding biosecurity. Biosecurity is not a word but it must become a regimented habit to protect your birds without any shortcuts. If you practice the same routine on entering a poultry house and exiting a poultry house, disinfecting vehicle tires, not allowing extra people, etc. onto the premises and protecting your birds from any wild birds, you can help diminish the risk to your birds.

Our domestic birds simply do not have defenses against this virus, while wild birds are not affected by it. Regardless of the size of your operation, or the number of bird pets you have, moving them inside is the best measure to try and help protect them. - Mod.TG

